ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Description of the phenotype for the subject
Total years of education
Pre- to post-satiation change in subjective desirability of satiated reward: (Target Desire3 - Target Desire2)
Pre- to post-satiation change in subjective desirability of non-satiated reward: (Neutral Desire3 - Neutral Desire2)
Pre- to post-satiation change in hunger: (Hunger3 - Hunger2)
Pre- to post-satiation change in fullness: (Fullness3 - Fullness2)
Calories consumed during satiation phase
Number of button-presses for the satiated reward during Pre-satiation
Number of button-presses for the satiated reward during Post-satiation
Number of button-presses for the non-satiated reward during Pre-satiation
Number of button-presses for the non-satiated reward during Post-satiation
Subjective desirability of satiated reward before Training phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of satiated reward before Pre-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of satiated reward after Satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of satiated reward after Post-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of non-satiated reward before Training phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of non-satiated reward before Pre-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of non-satiated reward after Satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective desirability of non-satiated reward after Post-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all; 5 = Moderately; 10 = Very much

ElementDescription: Subjective hunger before Training phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all hungry; 5 = Moderately hungry; 10 = Extremely hungry

ElementDescription: Subjective hunger before Pre-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all hungry; 5 = Moderately hungry; 10 = Extremely hungry

ElementDescription: Subjective hunger after Satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all hungry; 5 = Moderately hungry; 10 = Extremely hungry

ElementDescription: Subjective hunger after Post-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all hungry; 5 = Moderately hungry; 10 = Extremely hungry

ElementDescription: Subjective fullness before Training phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all full; 5 = Moderately full; 10 = Extremely full

ElementDescription: Subjective fullness before Pre-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all full; 5 = Moderately full; 10 = Extremely full

ElementDescription: Subjective fullness after Satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all full; 5 = Moderately full; 10 = Extremely full

ElementDescription: Subjective fullness after Post-satiation phase
Notes: 0 = Not at all full; 5 = Moderately full; 10 = Extremely full

ElementDescription: body mass index of subject
Notes: -9=Missing; -5=Item/Instrument not collected; -2=Not collected at this time point

ElementDescription: Eating Attitudes Test score
Total trials needed to reach criterion (10 of both rewards obtained) during the Training phase
Total calories consumed during the entire task
Devaluation score for the satiated reward: (Pre-Responses__Satiated minus Post-Responses__Satiated)
Devaluation score for the non-satiated reward: (Pre-Responses__Neutral minus Post-Responses__Neutral)
Number of both rewards obtained during the first quarter of the Training phase
Number of both rewards obtained during the second quarter of the Training phase
Number of both rewards obtained during the third quarter of the Training phase
Number of both rewards obtained during the fourth quarter of the Training phase
Subject's gender OTHER describe
